Titolo: Pokémon Rumble U

Anno: 2013

Descrizione: Pokémon Rumble U (ポケモンスクランブルU, Pokemon Sukuranburu U) is a 2013 action video game in the Pokémon series available on the Wii U eShop. It is the successor to the 2011 3DS game Pokémon Rumble Blast. It features all Pokémon from the first five generations. Up to 100 Pokémon and 4 players are able to play at the same time. It is the first Wii U game to utilize the Wii U GamePad's NFC function. It was released in Japan on April 24, 2013, in Europe on August 15, 2013, and in North America on August 29, 2013.